on reading compounds: 臣【オミ】retainer, attendant, Omi (hereditary title; orig. one of the two highest such titles, later demoted to sixth highest of eight), I, me
臣下【シンカ】retainer, subject, vassal, servant
忠臣【チュウシン】loyal retainer, loyal subject
重臣【ジュウシン】chief vassal, senior statesman
国務大臣【コクムダイジン】Minister of State
内大臣【ナイダイジン】Lord Keeper of the Privy Seal (1885-1945 CE), Minister of the Interior (669-1868 CE)
